---
import DocLayout from '../../layouts/DocLayout.astro';
---

<DocLayout title="Building Kayoko">
  <p class="text-xl font-light text-kayoko-muted mb-12">
    Kayoko uses a Lua-powered build orchestrator for high portability and speed. 
    The system is designed to be modular, allowing you to build individual components or the entire base system.
  </p>

  <h2 class="text-3xl mb-6">Quick Start</h2>
  <pre class="p-8 mb-4"><code>$ lua ./build.lua <coreutils|kernel|init|base|branding></code></pre>
  
  <div class="callout-tip">
    <strong class="text-black block mb-2 font-medium">Build Tip</strong>
    To add color to your logs, always append <code class="bg-kayoko-accent/40 px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded-sm">--color=always</code> to your command string. 
    This is especially helpful for tracking errors during long kernel compilations.
  </div>

  <h2 class="text-3xl mt-20 mb-8">Primary Targets</h2>
  <ul class="space-y-6">
    <li>
	    <strong class="font-medium text-black">kernel</strong> — Compiles the NetBSD-based core. (run <strong>branding</strong> before!)    </li>
    <li>
      <strong class="font-medium text-black">coreutils</strong> — The standard suite of Unix-like tools (ls, cat, mkdir, etc.) written for Kayoko.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong class="font-medium text-black">init</strong> — The system initialization daemon and service manager.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong class="font-medium text-black">base</strong> — A meta-target that builds kernel, coreutils, and init into a bootable image.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong class="font-medium text-black">branding</strong> — Brands the NetBSD kernel.   </li>
  </ul>

  <h2 class="text-3xl mt-24 mb-8">Build Environment</h2>
  <table class="w-full text-left border-collapse mb-32">
    <thead>
      <tr class="border-b border-kayoko-border">
        <th class="py-4 px-2 font-medium text-black">Dependency</th>
	<th class="py-4 px-2 font-medium text-black">Minimum Version / Edition</th>
      </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody class="divide-y divide-kayoko-border">
      <tr>
        <td class="py-5 px-2 font-mono text-sm">Lua</td>
        <td class="py-5 px-2 text-kayoko-muted">5.4+</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
	      <td class="py-5 px-2 font-mono text-sm">C++/CC</td>
        <td class="py-5 px-2 text-kayoko-muted">C11 and C++20 Compliant</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td class="py-5 px-2 font-mono text-sm">Make</td>
        <td class="py-5 px-2 text-kayoko-muted">GNU Make</td>
      </tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>
</DocLayout>
